Source: autoconf
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Tux Mason <tuxmason@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9)
Standards-Version: 3.9.5
Homepage: https://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf/autoconf.html

Package: autoconf
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCH
Depends: libc (>= 1.1.8), perl, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description:  an extensible package of M4 macros
 Autoconf is an extensible package of M4 macros that produce shell
 scripts to automatically configure software source code packages.
 .
 These scripts can adapt the packages to many kinds of UNIX-like
 systems without manual user intervention.

Package: autoconf-doc
Section: doc
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Recommends: man-db
Depends: autoconf (= ${binary:Version})
Description: documentation for autoconf
 This package provides info and man pages for autoconf.
